<p>This is the recommended choice for small leagues (6 teams or less), or leagues where all teams are theoretically equal in skill level and there are enough games in the season for every team to play every other team. There is also a scheduling option for round robin leagues which essentially splits the league in half, if there are only enough games for each team to play half of the other teams.</p>
<p>League standings are based on win/loss record.</p>
